<p>Think about the tu-dum sound you hear when you load Netflixâ€”thatâ€™s a great example of what a solid sonic identity can do for a brand. When that 3 second long sound didnâ€™t work for theaters, they had Hans Zimmer create an <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2020/8/13/21366371/netflix-sound-hans-zimmer-theaters-tadum-twenty-thousand-hertz-podcast-sound-design">extended version</a>.</p>
<p>Cadbury followed suit by having Guy Farley <a href="https://www.thedrum.com/news/2022/08/16/it-was-mad-men-pitch-scene-guy-farley-composing-cadbury-s-new-sonic-logo">drum up a sonic logo</a> that captured the brand.</p>
<p>While traditional jingles may be losing their appeal, thereâ€™s no denying that they worked.</p>
<p>And with brands trying to create a consistent <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/what-is-multichannel-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">multi-channel presence</a> across social media, TV, streaming, and radio, sonic branding might be the new jingle.</p>
<div id="howto"></div>
<h2>How to advertise on Spotify</h2>
<p>With Spotify Ad Studio, you can create an audio or a video (horizontal or vertical) ad.</p>
<p>Hereâ€™s how to use the self-serve ad manager, Spotify Ad Studio, to create an audio or video ad.</p>
<h3>Step 1: Create an account (if you have one already, skip this step)</h3>
<p>Make a <a href="https://www.spotify.com/us/signup" target="_blank" rel="noopener">free Spotify account</a>. Use Google, Facebook, or your email to sign up.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-create-account.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - create account homepage" width="497" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73584" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-create-account.jpg 497w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-create-account-480x579.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 497px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Once youâ€™ve logged in, you will be able to access the <a href="https://ads.spotify.com/en-US/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ad Studio</a>, which will allow you to create individual ads or complex campaigns that involve ad sets.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-ad-studio-campaigns.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - campaigns page" width="936" height="549" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73585" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-ad-studio-campaigns.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-ad-studio-campaigns-480x282.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Step 2: Add campaign details</h3>
<p>Name your campaign and tell Spotify what youâ€™re advertising.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-new-campaign.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - create campaign name" width="936" height="556" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73586" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-new-campaign.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-new-campaign-480x285.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Fill in the ad set name and declare an ad category (the ad category helps Spotify deliver relevant ads to listeners).</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-ad-set-details.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - enter ad set details" width="936" height="534" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73587" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-ad-set-details.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-ad-set-details-480x274.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Step 3: Set your target audience</h3>
<p>Select the right location(s). You can choose specific regions or countries.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-audiences.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - specify audience" width="936" height="548" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73588" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-audiences.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-audiences-480x281.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>If youâ€™re running a nationwide campaign, you can also add postal codes in bulk (up to 1,000 locations) by typing or copying and pasting them.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-add-postal-codes.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - batch enter postal codes" width="520" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73589" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-add-postal-codes.jpg 520w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-add-postal-codes-480x554.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 520px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Choose the age group(s) and gender(s) you want to target.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-age-gender.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - choose age and gender of audience" width="936" height="500" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73590" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-age-gender.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-age-gender-480x256.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Narrow down the interests and behaviors of your audience.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-interests-behaviors.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - include interests and behaviors" width="936" height="580" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73591" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-interests-behaviors.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-interests-behaviors-480x297.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>If you select no additional targeting, you will be able to reach the broadest audience. Selecting one of the other options will help you serve your ad to a more relevant segment. For instance, if you choose contextual playlists, your ad will only be played during specific activities when listeners play a themed playlist.</p>
<p>Next, choose the language you want to target.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-language.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - choose language for ads" width="936" height="274" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73592" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-language.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-language-480x141.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Select the platform(s) where you want to serve your ad.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-platforms.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - choose platform for ads" width="936" height="241" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73593" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-platforms.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-platforms-480x124.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Step 4: Choose the format and placement of the ad</h3>
<p>You have three formats to choose from: audio, horizontal, and vertical video. While Spotify recommends you choose the automatic placement, i.e., your ad will run across music and podcasts, you can opt to place your ad in music streams only.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-format-placement.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - specify format and placement of ad" width="936" height="465" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73594" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-format-placement.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-format-placement-480x238.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>You also have control over whether you want to exclude your ads from playing during certain podcast episodes that may not align with your brand. Similarly, you can add topics that make sense for your brand values and offer <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/02/06/personalized-marketing">personalized experiences</a> to listeners.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-podcast-episode-topics.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - choose any podcast content controls" width="602" height="598" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73595" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-podcast-episode-topics.jpg 602w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-podcast-episode-topics-480x477.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 602px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Step 5: Create the ad schedule and set the budget</h3>
<p>You can choose to run the ad indefinitely or select a start and end date and time.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-schedule-ad.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - schedule ad " width="936" height="417" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73596" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-schedule-ad.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-schedule-ad-480x214.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>The minimum average daily budget is $15 and the minimum lifetime budget is $250. You can enter a custom amount. Based on the audience, Spotify can predict whether youâ€™ll spend some or all of your budget.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-budget.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - choose budget" width="853" height="598" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73597" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-budget.jpg 853w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-budget-480x337.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 853px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Step 6: Choose a delivery objective<strong>Â </strong></h3>
<p>You can select one of three delivery goals for Spotify to prioritize: impressions, reach, or clicks.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-objective.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - choose objective for ad" width="635" height="599" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73598" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-objective.jpg 635w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-objective-480x453.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 635px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>You also get to set the frequency cap (how frequently the ad will appear per day, per week, and per month) and the bid cap.</p>
<p>Spotify offers recommendations for the bid amount based on similar audiences.</p>
<h3>Step 7: Create your ad</h3>
<p>Fill in the ad details like ad name, advertiser name, and tagline, and choose the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/04/13/call-to-action-examples">CTA</a>. Set the destination URL and tracking URL (optional).</p>
<p>You can see an example of what the ad preview looks like at this stage:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-ad-details.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - create your add" width="603" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73599" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-ad-details.jpg 603w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-ad-details-480x478.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 603px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Add a companion image thatâ€™ll appear while the ad plays and your logo (optional). These images should be in JPG or PNG format and at least 640 x 640 pixels.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-image-logo.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - add image and logo" width="739" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73600" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-image-logo.jpg 739w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-image-logo-480x390.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 739px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Hereâ€™s what the preview looks like when those images are uploaded:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-ad-preview.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - ad preview example" width="320" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73601" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-ad-preview.jpg 320w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-ad-preview-160x300.jpg 160w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" /></p>
<p>Since we chose audio as the ad format, weâ€™ll show you the options you have:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-add-audio.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - add audio for ad" width="604" height="599" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73602" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-add-audio.jpg 604w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-add-audio-480x476.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 604px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>The first option is pretty straightforward. You can upload your audio or choose one from the library.</p>
<p>But the â€œCreate Audioâ€ option is a game-changer for businesses. You donâ€™t even need a script or an in-house voice actor. Spotify can write one for you and produce your ad in 2-4 business days.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-creative-brief.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - creative brief" width="321" height="599" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73603" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-creative-brief.jpg 321w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-creative-brief-161x300.jpg 161w" sizes="(max-width: 321px) 100vw, 321px" /></p>
<p>If you choose video as the ad format, you also get the option to enable viewability tracking thanks to third-party vendors along with the optional tracking URL.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-viewability-tracking.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - viewability tracking" width="936" height="491" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73604" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-viewability-tracking.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-viewability-tracking-480x252.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>You can use drag and drop the video to upload the content&#8211;no hidden bells and whistles there.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-upload-video.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - upload video ad" width="936" height="346" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73605" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-upload-video.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-upload-video-480x177.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Step 8: Add your business address and payment information</h3>
<p>Once you add this information, you can then submit your ad for approval.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-add-payment.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - how to run spotify ads - add business info and payment info" width="936" height="514" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73606" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-add-payment.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-setup-add-payment-480x264.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="tips"></div>
<h2>Tips to tune into success with Spotify advertising</h2>
<p>Due to â€œthe carryover effect,â€ Spotify listeners are just as engaged while listening to ads as they were while streaming music or binging on podcasts. <a href="https://storage.pardot.com/52662/1677552207ZGvhSQfc/Sonic_Science_US.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">60%</a> of the ad engagement is carried over from what listeners consumed before.</p>
<p>In short, youâ€™ve got a highly receptive audience thatâ€™s willing to engage with your ad. Apart from the usual advice&#8211;mention your brand, include a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/10/05/best-call-to-action-phrases">strong CTA</a>, and stay on message&#8211;here are some data-backed best practices you may want to use.</p>
<h3>Mix audio, video, and display</h3>
<p>Your best bet at holding your audienceâ€™s attention and making it count is to combine different ad formats for your Spotify advertising campaigns.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-ad-recall-chart.jpg" alt="spotify advertising - ad recall for spotify audio and video ads" width="786" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73607" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-ad-recall-chart.jpg 786w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-ad-recall-chart-480x366.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 786px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://ads.spotify.com/en-US/news-and-insights/dentsu-research-attention-economy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p><a href="https://ads.spotify.com/en-US/news-and-insights/dentsu-research-attention-economy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dentsuâ€™s study</a> has proven that Spotifyâ€™s ability to run ads in different formats yields those benchmark-breaking metrics.</p>
<h3>Donâ€™t skimp on the ad creative</h3>
<p>Strong ad creative is the biggest lever you can pull when it comes to making an engaged audience convert. Dentsuâ€™s data showed that a poor creative can cause a <a href="https://ads.spotify.com/en-US/news-and-insights/dentsu-research-attention-economy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">17%</a> decline in ad recall.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-ad-creative-example.jpg" alt="spotify advertising ad creative examples" width="778" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73608" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-ad-creative-example.jpg 778w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/spotify-advertising-ad-creative-example-480x370.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 778px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://ads.spotify.com/en-IN/ad-experiences/sponsored-sessions-specs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>Spotify allows you to create compelling ads with free built-in creative tools like background music and 3D audio (AKA the surround sound effect) and deliver them in an engaging format like Homepage Takeover or Overlay.</p>
<h3>Let the genre guide you</h3>
<p>Since audio ads have a 55-70 word range, you have to be economical with your choice of words. You donâ€™t want to sound rushed or breathless, so edit with a heavy hand.</p>
<p>Knowing your audience well can help with that. If youâ€™re going to serve ads to sports fans, you might want to play up the energy and sprinkle in some sports metaphors. But if the goal is to get in front of an audience that prioritizes wellness, you want to adopt a calm, soothing tone. 73% of the Sonic Science study participants were willing to listen to an ad if the tone fits their current activity.</p>
<h3>Write for real peopleâ€™s ears</h3>
<p>Your priority is to connect with real listeners. Remember not to let rigid brand guidelines eliminate the human element from your script.</p>
<p>Use contractions, colloquialisms, and hang up the grammarian hat for a while. Infuse the script with your personality, a little bit of humor, and bring that main character energy.</p>
